title: $A down as US Fed leaves rates unchanged
text:
Thu, Jul 30, 2015, 7:02 AM AEST - Australia Markets open in 2 hrs 58 mins $A down as US Fed leaves rates unchanged AAP â€“ 11 minutes ago Print 
The Australian dollar is lower after the US Federal Reserve left interest rates unchanged but kept a September rate rise on the table. 
At 0630 AEST on Thursday, the currency was trading at 72.97 US cents, down from 73.21 US cents on Friday. 
The Fed kept its benchmark federal funds interest rate unchanged at near zero per cent as expected, providing no new clues on the timing of a long awaited rate rise, which is expected later this year. 
CURRENCY SNAPSHOT AT 0630 AEST ON THURSDAY 
One Australian dollar buys: 
* 72.97 US cents, from 73.21 cents on Wednesday 
* 90.42 Japanese yen, from 90.52 yen 
* 66.41 euro cents, from 66.28 euro cents 
(*Currency closes taken at 1700 AEST previous local session)
